title: Lopes Houses & Huts
name: Lopes Houses & Huts
description: Very high-resolution imagery of the three VHR sites was used to identify houses and small huts. Information on their type, amount and distribution is valuable for a more efficient indoor residual spraying (IRS). With such spatial information, the amount and type of insecticides (depend on structure type) needed per area can be better estimated and the progress and status of IRS coverage can be monitored. However, an automated mapping of households is very challenging in rural areas, since most of the structures are very small, with varying shape (round or squared) and with manifold roof types that are hard to distinguish from background materials (e.g. reed roofs). An intensive literature review showed that there is no tested image analysis approach feasible to detect small houses and huts in rural areas. In MALAREO, an object-based approach for an automated house/hut detection basing on VHR data was developed using geometric, topological and spectral features. Round and squared structures were differentiated, since the shape of a structure is a good indicator for the structure type (round structures are mostly reed roofed clay huts and squared structures are mostly bricked houses with corrugated roofs). In order to achieve high classification accuracies, over-detections have been evaluated and manually corrected. Data source: (c) IKONOS(2011), provided under EC/ESA GSC-DA.
